For this homework, we will be using the msleep dataset from the ggplot2 package. This dataset contains information about the sleep habits of various mammals. Reference: V. M. Savage and G. B. West. A quantitative, theoretical framework for understanding mammalian sleep. Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences, 104 (3):1051-1056, 2007.

3. Make a plot that shows the number of mammals in each vore type. Which vore type is most represented in the data?

ggplot(data=msleep, mapping=aes(x=vore))+
  geom_bar(mapping=aes(fill=vore))

labs(title="Number of mammals in each vore type",x="Vore type",y="Count")
## <ggplot2::labels> List of 3
##  $ x    : chr "Vore type"
##  $ y    : chr "Count"
##  $ title: chr "Number of mammals in each vore type"

herbi is most represented. 4. What is the average length of time that each mammal sleeps?

avg_sleep <- mean(msleep$sleep_total)
avg_sleep
## [1] 10.43373

Avg sleep time is 10.4 hrs. 5. Use summary() to get a quick idea of the range of values for the variable bodywt.

6. Build a plot that shows the range of bodywt. by vore type. Because the range of bodywt is so variable, you will need to scale the y-axis. You do this by adding scale_y_log10() as another layer.

ggplot(data=msleep, mapping=aes(x=vore,y=bodywt))+
  geom_boxplot(mapping=aes(fill=vore))+
  labs(title="Body weight by vore type",x="Vore type",y="Body weight")+
  scale_y_log10()

7. Is there a relationship between body weight and total sleep time? Add appropriate labels and a title to your plot.

ggplot(data=msleep, mapping=aes(x=bodywt,y=sleep_total))+
  geom_point(mapping=aes())+
  geom_smooth(method=lm, se=T)+
  labs(title="Body weight vs. total sleep time",x="Body weight",y="Total sleep time")+
  scale_x_log10()
## `geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ x'

There is a negative relationship between body weight and sleep time (as body weight inc, sleep time dec) 8. Which vore type tends to sleep the most? Build a plot to support your answer.

ggplot(data=msleep, mapping=aes(x=vore,y=sleep_total))+
  geom_boxplot(mapping=aes(fill=vore))+
  labs(title="Sleep total by vore type",x="Vore type",y="Sleep total")

The insecti vore tends to sleep the most. 9. Is there a relationship between brain weight and body weight? Build a plot to support your answer.

ggplot(data=msleep, mapping=aes(x=brainwt,y=bodywt))+
  geom_point()+
  geom_smooth(method=lm)+
  labs(title="Brain weight vs body weight",x="Brain weight",y="Body weight")+
  xlim(0, 1.5) + ylim(0, 750)
